originalText.text: Awful management. Unresponsive and unhelpful. Had an incident where water was leaking through our ceiling from a broken pipe above, first noticed the issue in October, repeatedly emailed our property manager for help with the leak and took forever to get the issue attended to. The wall and ceiling were simply patched up, no attendance to the root of the issue. End of March, ceiling and walls formed huge water bubbles again from leak, quickly deteriorating to full ceiling breakage and water rushing out from ceiling. Maintenance came by to fix and tore the ceiling open to fix the main issue, but the main management office did not pick up the phone (called multiple times in a row in the middle of business hours) and Brendan (property manager whom we were referred to contact in case of apartment EMERGENCIES) was called several times, again no pick up, PLUS was sending us to voicemail????? While our ceiling was on the verge of collapsing…. Have never actually had the pleasure of speaking to Brendan on the phone because he never once answered a call. Management did not respond at all to several of our emails with various apartment concerns (huge roach issue even for an NYC apartment, pests, the whole ceiling collapse thing) and again did not respond when we expressed concern that the leak could’ve involved waste water, which usually involves hazmat cleanup! Instead, our sweet maintenance man cleaned up the mess without so much as a mask to protect himself. Not worth your money, your time, your effort, anything. Horrible and neglectful. Do not sign a lease with them, you will get screwed.

originalText.text: Worst Management company.  They are unresponsive, unprofessional and ineffective.  I have been trying to contact Ian Johnson, the property manager for various ongoing complaints and he still has not had the professional courtesy to call me to discuss my issues.  Every time there is an issue to be fixed the contractor promise to come and fix something, I take off from work only to be stood up.  I am infuriated. Garbage has been in the hallway attracting mice for over two months. The bathroom ceiling leaks and causes holes and mold every year. The only reason they fix that is because I submit a 3-1-1 complaint.  There is a serious electrical issue and I am worried it might cause a fire.  I have sent dozen of emails to voice my concerns.  Worst Management Company!
